values: This is the first time in quite awhile that i have felt truly happy, on a deeper level. Obama is the next president. It couldn't have happened at a better time. We need change, and I really hope he can come through and be an FDR type of president. Although I am excited and inspired I'm not going to rub it in Republicans faces. They should know by now they have done wrong, or not well.They are so much ruder, and immature about everything. When McCain gave his speech (which seemed genuine and articulate) people BOOed as he congratulated obama. you don't see democrats doing that because we have more sense. Obama is under so much pressure, and he has a lot to work on in order to get this country going again, but i think he has the knowledge and the tenacity to do it. He will be scrutinized for everything because he is black. if one thing goes wrong i feel like everyone will jump all over him. but im glad to trust the next four years in his hands. its about fucking time.

Tomorrow I will have been home a week and i still dont know what to do. I worked a little this week, which helped get my mind off stuff, but I'm just bored and lonely and miss my best friend. It's weird because when i talk to him i picture exactly where he is in the apartment, or walking to steinway street, or in the subway. i dont know if that helps me or hurts because its so much more specific. Tomorrow is Halloween, my favorite holiday. I want to go out and have a great night but i dont know if it will work out that way.

i feel like i wont be able to go out without taking a xanax. but if i take xanax i wont be able to drink. and that always gets weird. you get the same questions:
1) are you religious?
2) are you pregnant?
3) is someone in your family an alcoholic?
4) are you straight edge?

there should be a number five on there

5) Are you not drinking because you had a slight mental breakdown from living in new york city and you are unable to handle simple tasks because you have so much anxiety you cant function, especially in social situations like this one, so you self medicate to get through an evening that should be a fun time with friends so you abuse xanax before the party so you can make it to the party and then realize you shouldnt drink while on a bunch of xanax?

its not necessarily peer pressure, but people that are drinking always judge the non-drinkers. i have definitely done it to the non-drinkers, whether that was their lifestyle choice or they had a test the next day or something. i only went to a handful of parties where i was completey sober while in college- it was usually because i went out too late and didnt feel like catching up with drinking at 1am, so i just didnt do it. occasionally i was still hungover from the night before, but someone in my group would always counter that excuse with "the best way to cure a hangover is to keep drinking!" i tried it, but it didnt really work for me. so im going to be that girl at the party. the awkward non-drinker. or ill be the drunk girl that goes crazy when she has a panic attack from drinking. either way im not going to be making any new friends tomorrow.

so it seems like whenever I'm home I write in this bullshit. I'm generally depressed when I'm home.

This time, I came back home after living in New York City, which is worse than Cave Creek. Who would have thought. I don't really know what to do now. I miss Ryan. I'm thinking I'll probably return to California in a few months when i get my head straight, and just hope that Ryan doesnt meet someone or break up with me in the meantime. I guess i can't worry about it until it happens. 

I really fucking hate nyc and I'm so glad i left. i just wish ryan would have come with me.

so i leave to start my semester in spain in a few weeks. I have my visa. Luckily I'm in a dorm (thank god). i miss ryan. i feel weird looking on sites that contain pictures such as facebook, myspace, or even good old fashioned lj, and everyone always has like an album of them making out with their significant other. am i weird for not having any of these pictures online, or having never taken any at all?
I am so sick of working. But i really am enjoying the money. Ryan isnt coming out for my 21st, but i cant really hold it against him. south carolina is pretty far away.

Could i get any more bored? Ive been home 9 days and im ready to do something else. go somewhere else. do something. bored bored bored. i bet this will make me fat.

On the upside, I have been able to read for leisure.
On the downside, all the books so far have sucked.

Everything is sort of ridiculous. Not to mention boring. I always feel so shitty when i come home, its nice for like the first two hours, after i hug everyone and pet my meows and take off my shoes. its lovely being able to walk around clean surfaces, i always have some sort of footwear on at school, even in my apartment just cause i have this thing with floor cleanliness, despite otherwise being a generally disgusting human being. its also nice using toilet paper thats super soft. 
i miss ryan, and i feel really lame about it, but we do spend a lot of time together.
everyone is still in school, or preoccupied with it. i need money but im not going to start working until after i come back from south carolina.

theres so much sluttiness in the world. i wish i was a part of it.

Goin' to Az tomorrow for break. It'll be nice but I'm still stressed out a bit. I'm basically just going to be doing homework in a new location...hooray. And my sister wont be there. And no one is on break. I'm going blind and not feeling that great about it. I'm so proud of myself for not drinking tonight, driving that long hungover is not fun. I need to get my plans for the summer organized. I miss brennaa!
I'm filling out my study abroad application for next fall. I'm already really excited about it, but also bummed out cause its my senior year and i will miss out on a lot. que sera sera adivino!

Although being home is generally boring, there are some reminders of why I come back. 
...But i still miss people at school and I'm not looking forward to returning to my apartment with two brand new roommates. Sigh.

I'm gonna go draw.

I've been out of the lj community for a long time, all this crazy shit is on it now. I feel I don't need to write in this because all I do is write. Just not on the internet. That's cool. Alright. I'M ARTSY

Back at school. It's been glorious and horrendous at the same time...all my classes seem to being going well, I'm not quite sure about Spanish though. I only have one class on friday, but its at nine thirty. Not cool. I was not looking forward to taking Poetry, but now i look forward to it. It's so different from fiction, and i hope it will help me be flexible and incorporate more elements into my fiction. 

My apartment is sweet, My roommates kick fucking ass. However, we will probably be evicted on Wednesday if we don't get another roommate. After extensive facebook stalking ( which is semi-ironic since facebook has indeed become quasi-"big brother" on defenseless college kids around the country) we might have found some chick willing to live with us. i fucking hope so. i dont really want to live on campus. and i already changed my meal plan.

lame.

Working is being tedious since I am only recieving $2.13 for my "hardworking" efforts. I need some cash money quick, due to my evergrowing ebay addiction. Nobody wants to drive to LA with me on thursday to see Alkaline Trio. psh, they call themselves fans. Watching gatorade commercials almost motivate me enough to be active. almost. It's only been a few days but I already miss a bunch of people. Sigh.

I don't even know if I'm ready but i feel like i should be ready for something. Only a few more days until I'm in AZ, this should be an interesting summer to say the least. well, i hope so anyway. When I'm home all i want to do is be anywhere that isnt cave creek. Sometimes I truly hate southern california, but it's pretty accessible to other cooler places. Basically i have come to the realization that it's pretty much impossible for me to be happy, anywhere. I am that lame.

I'm so done with college. I'm going to be so happy next year when I'm taking all the classes I want to take for my major, no more LAFs! Wee! Poetry is going to suck though. I just can't do that genre at all. I still have two years left of college, and I'm having so much fun I don't want to leave. But at the same time I do. I want to work for a cool magazine, and write fiction on the side. I hope this happens. Just depends on how bad i want it. My mom wanted me to fly back to PHX for easter. She bought me a ticket and everything but she's having me miss a day of school so i had to decline. I have finals and I'll be home for like ten days after that before may term. Lame. We don't even do anything at Easter. We arent religious. It would be a waste of time. And i only have a few weeks left with people who wont be here for may term. This weather has really been bringing me down. The haze and darkness and clouds and cold weather. All around thumbs down. Thats not how I roll. Last year at this time i was sunbathing on the quad so what the fuck?! I have three essays due tomorrow. It's one thirty pm. And I'm going to take a nap instead.

So basically, last weekend was midterms. In order to celebrate this, and increase my academic struggles, Ryan and i peaced out and went to Vegas. It's only like three hours from school, so it was cake. The main point of going was not drinking and dicking around, despite what most think. It was to see Social Distortion. And it was awesome. I wish they would have played FOREVER. A great time to be had. I would really like to be a rockabilly girl. I don't think i could draw on my eyebrows everyday though. Bummer.



i don't think my pictures are working

oh snap. not much has changed.I'm at home and its been surprisingly fun for the most part, since i decided not to get all weirded out about it like last year. Ive had some practice since i was home all summer...anyway, been hanging out with Ki a lot which has been fabulous, made me realize how much i truly missed her. ive been shopping, with money i dont have, or watching other people shop. muy intersante. Ryan got in last night so hopefully I'll be able to see him in the next few days. Irena and i hung out with Ian last night, and that was a lot of fun. Although i think it brought back some crappy high school memories for everyone. But fun regardless. That kid is ridiculously good looking. On another note, my brother and his wench left this morning. She was a bitch. Everyone hated her. She doesn't treat my brother very well. That shit doesn't fly in our family. Cancelled Christmas was actually really fun. Had a bunch of friends over and everyone got kinda shitty and we played catch phrase for about 6 hours. Good Times. It's weird being home and being able to drink free, nice booze. I feel classier, even if i am drinking in my parents house. ha. Hope New Years is fun, and perhaps i will resolute. 

The best thing of all is that i got my grades. I finished with a 3.6 this semester which means I DON'T have to go to ASU. That means I'm staying at u of r. woot!

Wow. This semester has been crazy. Crazy good though. It will soon be finals week, so procrastination is at an all time high, so that is why i come crawling back to you beloved LJ. Turns out, creative writing is harder than i thought. I'm totally freaking out tryin to revise shit for my portfolio. I get to go to AZ on the 17, which i have mixed signals about. I want to go for the people! I.e. parental units, my brother who i havent seen in 6 months, my sister, Irena, and Ryan i guess. Other than that, az doesn't do it for me anymore. Theres really nothing for me. I think I'm going to move to L.A. after school. I don't know why I'm thinking about my future so much when i still have 2 years left. Oh, and I'm officially addicted to nip/tuck. great. just what i need.

I don't know what's wrong with me. I have just been fucking restless these past few weeks. Sleeping, studying, sitting, drinking. i feel like all i do is sit. to eat. to watch movies. class. at my computer. when im waiting for someone. meetings. DO I HAVE LEGS ANYMORE?! I could get cellulite from this. disgusting. my pictures of all the people i miss/ good times i have keep falling off my wall... IS THIS A BAD SIGN!? im taking it as one, and I'm sure if kiki was here she would say the same.i think i hope i pray my classes are going well since its november already (!) two more years and then im out in the real world. so scary. especially since all my friend will be at grad/law/medical school. ive said it before ill say it again, i dont need companionship of the opposite sex. fuck that. fuck them. meanies. see? im reduced to using a word like ''meanie'' to describe them, how out of character is that? someone got carjacked in my parking lot next to my dorm at gunpoint. bummer. food has been bad. i am so sick of eating. im so sick of thinking about what i want to eat. i miss my sister. i miss my litty. i miss ki. i miss ryan too but hes the easiest to put out of my mind. i have to advise my freshman again, and if last time was any indicator, its going to blow. im going to go be listless in another room.

blerg. i really hate midterms. ive got so much shit to do. plus i have to write for the paper and all that crap. the weather has been icky. rainy. cold. generally not the weather i want on the west coast. this weekend was awful and amazing at the same time. besides getting into major drama at the ska house. fallfest was on sunday so i had tons of fun seeing bad religion. we couldnt get an interview though. this depressed me. but ill live. it wasnt meant to be. i got backstage and stuff though so that was cool. Im never drinking jager again.

Long time. Long time i know. I haven't even written in my paper journal since August, but thats not as important since I'm in a workshop and turn that shit in for a grade. Let's see...school is raping me up the ass. ''Hey is your ass bleeding?'' ''Umm no...?'' ''Mine is because i just got RAPED by that test'' ahh high school memories. But seriously. Five classes. Madness. Sure i get paid for one, but it doesnt mean much considering how much work i do. i LOVE this campus i love how its beautiful and perfect everyday. I love my dorm. I love my friends. I love how i can explore California on my free time. Speaking of which, fall break is this weekend! hooray! So I'm driving to Santa Barbara to hang out with Lauren, who i havent seen in years. I'm so fucking excited! Everyone is getting sick, so hopefully i can make it out of here without bringing the germs with me...who wants to be sick on fall break? Not i. I miss my sister and Kiki mucho. Last weekend we had tons of fun at stefanies house party, although drama ensued. Lame. I love how when you light up a joint at a party, 15 people casually walk over and ''introduce'' themselves. haha Things with adam are going ok i think, which is nice, considering i have no idea how they are supposed to be going. i went to the BOUNCING SOULS concert at the el rey in los angeles on sunday. it was fucking amazing. Great concert, 7 seconds was really good as well as the street dogs. The venue was so gorgeous, with glass chandieliers and stuff, so it was hilarious seeing the contrast of all that old world beauty amidst gutter punks. I put my nose ring in and busted out the fishnets. Hardcore, i know. i want this week to be over. Stat. Is it friday at four oclock yet?

Who the fuck dates someone for an entire summer and even as i type and then not fucking tell someone about it? Who does that? And then lies about the fact that they aren't seeing someone even when you inquire regularly? Oh i know, maybe it's because you should be ashamed for dating someone that cheated on you and shat on your fucking heart, and know that if you tell that shit to someone like me they are automatically going to think youre a dumb motherfucker. If you love her so goddamn much then why are you fucking ashamed or embarassed or whatever it is to say it? You should be declaring that shit from the rooftops, and while you're up there don't mind me when i give you a push off because thats where you deserve to be. If you come back I'm not going to be there. Don't touch me and think of her. If you pretend hard enough I won't turn into her, and I'm glad because I don't ever want to be her, even if that means I'll never be with you. Are you keeping her around as the inspiration for the teen angst factor? You're a piece of shit. HOW ABOUT YOU GO WRITE A SONG ABOUT THAT

Fucking A bitches! Being back in SoCal is awesome. I truly love it. Miss my friends and my delightful roomie, can't wait till they all come in on Monday...Peer advising/training has been crazy. Seriously. I'm working atleast 8-6 everyday. The freshman class is hot though and i have no problem with cradle robbing. Went up to the cabin for a couple days to see the bro/ spend time with loey. It was fun, but ten days a year with a sibling is not enough. Stupid bob. Anyway i flew back, had two days and then dad and i drove out and unpacked. I missed being able to move loey in this year but she had bob so I'm sure it was cool. I have three classes on Fridays...why does god hate me?

So basically we headed down to B.F.E (or B.F.M., whereas ''M'' clearly stands for Malaysia) Peoria to hang out...It was crazy fun, and madness as always.

 

Ahh I miss dora...

 

And of course my favorite Serbian Hippie...

Needless to say though, its hard to bask in one's awesomeness which is precisely what we are doing...

 

Woot Woot!

Who would have thought. So it's been awhile, but in a nutshell not much has changed. I still hate my job/am broke. I'm done house sitting, so that's a relief. Went to the Alkaline Trio concert and it was fucking AWESOME! Just as it should have been. Matt is prettttty hot. I had so much fun with Lo and Vinny, who is an awesome bodyguard. They played so many great songs, but I am definitely not drinking before a show again. I'll pass. 
Ryan came last week, i saw him twice. It was bittersweet. It almost would have been easier for me if hadn't seen him, since I miss him so much. I called him on Friday to wish him a safe trip home, and after that i promised myself i wouldn't call him or text him. I was doing damn good! Not thinking about him and stuff, and then he fucking calls me tonight...down the drain again. So I am starting from scratch. 
Lately, i have become aware that numerous movies were filmed on my lovely campus, so i have been watching them. Examples include: Slackers, and Rules of Attraction. It's crazy. 
I have been hanging out with Ki more which has been much needed for me anyway...
Only a couple more weeks and then i get to go see my brother...what what?! Then i get to go to school early for training...It should be fun though, maybe I'll meet more cool people? Is that possible?
Excellent. 
Apparently i need jaw surgery..wtf?
On another note, my liver is thanking me for the break...awww

WELL. I am not thrilled with my job. I don't feel as bad though, since most of my other employed friends are not feeling their jobs this summer either. This is the first job I've had where i genuinely do not look forward to going to work. Whateves. Life is really weird right now, I'm missing my Redlands crew, but at the same time I'm missing my Az Crew because go figure, a lot of the people i wanted to spend time with are abroad. This brings me to my next dilema. Parental units are going out of town for fourth of july weekend. Naturally, Lo and i will be partying it up. However, they will all be Lo's friends, since mine won't really be around. So, to whoever is reading this, you should come to my house and party. There's a bunch of movies i still want to see but most of them nobody else wants to see. HERMPF. Well I'm gonna go hang out with Ki. Hooray!

Well. It's storming and raining up here in the boonies, and its quite nice to hear rain and thunder. Reminds me of my rainy year in So Cal. I got a job. Finally. Carefree Station. I'm not making much money but hopefully i will get a lot of hours. I had the weirdest yet best birthday ever, two days ago. I woke up went out to lunch with my Grandma, got ready and started my first day at work. It was crazy and i never got trained, they just threw me to the wolves. Luckily, after three years of hostessing i kinda know what the fuck I'm doing. Basically same thing, different table numbers. I really would rather be serving but I'm only gonna be here for a little bit. Naturally, the only guy i was flirting with turns out to be 26. That's a bit too old for me. Oh well. It's easy, just really boring. So i walk out to my truck, I'm talking to my sister on the phone and there is a bouquet of flowers on my lock box. It was such a great surprise, and they were from my one and only Serbian! Then i drove home and hung out with my parents and sister and Kiki (well my dad was actually on the couch, but he was like within 20 feet of us, so I'm gonna tally him anyway). Lo is taking me to Alkaline Trio!!!!!!!! HOORAY! I'm so excited to see a concert with her, just like old times! We aren't going to the Warped Tour this year, no good bands. I got a digital camera so that was cool as well. Probably the best part of my birthday was finding out how many people care about me...haha. My brother, out of all people started calling me at 7am to wish me a Happy Birthday, and kept calling me till i finally picked up. It was sweet considering he never remembers this kind of stuff, or pretends he doesn't give a fuck. Umm let's see Harley not only called me, but sent me something. Brenna called me. Ali called me at midnight, Ryan texted me at midnight, so 3 am his time, then called me later that day. Ki texted me and called me of course. Stefano called me. Jasper called me. I talked to Liz numerous times. And the list goes on. Usually everyone forgets, so hooray! Don't squash my dreams by saying that the only reason these people remembered was because the facebook sent them messages. Bitches. Today i woke up at one pm and went to work. I really miss Tonto. God thats so pathetic saying that but i reallly do. Ryan said hes going to try to go back to U of R for fall, which would be awesome but i truly doubt he will. My sister and i have opposite schedules so i never get to see her anymore, or she goes to bed early since B of A consists of Nazis. Oh LOOEEEYYY
Going to have a great night. In the bar. With my best friend.

Ok. So i have been back home for like a week or something like that. It's weird for sure. The last day on campus was stressful, and it sucked moving out all my stuff. Amazing, it all fit in the rah so that was good. I didn't even leave CA until 5PM, so i got home like 10. I was convinced my snowboard fell out somewhere in Indio. However, i pulled up to a stoplight in Wickenburg and i saw it, so hooray for me. Then I went and picked up Ali at the airport the next day and we hung out for six days. Sadly, Az is really boring in comparison to San Diego, but it was still good to spend time with her. We hung out with Liz and Stefano a couple times, but they were both being really weird...I've been trying to get a job, i guess El Encanto is showing the most hope. I just know im broke nigga, I'M BROKE! Parents out of town starting tomorrow, so there could be small gatherings taking place at my house. Excellent. I talked to Ryan a couple days ago and hes coming out to AZ in July maybe, so I'm excited. Haven't seen much of Kiki, and when i do she seems preoccupied, so i hope shes doin ok. I bought a dress today, it has polka dots on it, and that's all you need to know.

I think my final is due tomorrow. I am uncertain since i slept through my alarm today, and did not attend class. Therefore i do not know. However, i think I am going to try and finish it tonight, just to be on the safe side. Good idea? I think so. I am coming home quite soon, and have massive amounts of shit to complete before this time arrives. I hope the rah rah can hold all my shit. I am not bringing back as much shit to college next year. I didn't use half of it. It just took up space. Stupid Stupid. We got caught for alcohol on our last Saturday night here. It blew, especially since the RD IS A BITCH. She searched our room and sassed us, and made us open up our fridge. She took all our liquor. We have a meeting with her at 9:15 tonite. fucked up. Jon has been here all weekend, so that's been cool. I really need a job. Bad. I need to continue the homework process.

I'm sick again. My throat is sore, my stomach hurts, my head is throbbing, and I am producing hardcore amounts of mucous. It's lovely. Anyway, Thursday was pretty fun, Brenna and i drove to Orange County and hung out with her friend Nick, and went to this huge house party at her friend Wes' house. Madness. Brenna has some hot friends fo sho! We had a lot of fun, almost got in a fight on the way out, pretended to be lesbians at one point in order to ward of weirdos....good times. Then the three of us crammed into Nick's bed, and Brenna and I drove back to school at like 7:30am so I could attend class...Eww. Friday we all just relaxed and hung out and watched some movies. Saturday we got up and drove up to Big Bear to stay with Stefano's hot snowboarder friend John...and madness ensued. It was so fucking great be in another location, the weather was gorgeous, it smelled like pine cones. While we were driving up through the winding mountains, windows down, music up, screaming to songs at the top of our lungs it felt so great. I looked at my friends who mean so much to me now and just smiled. This is how college is supposed to be.

 

El Fin...
Orange County on Thursday. Big Bear today. I love California

Ok. So. Friday was cool i guess. I slept most of the day after class, then showered and we all got ready to make ourselves presentable to society. Then we (Liz, Ali, me, Jasper, Stefano, and Harley) went to Duke's Ball for Liz's Maroon and Grey thing. We basically just hung out and ate chocolate covered strawberries and listened to some good jazz music. Then Ali and went to Starbucks all dressed up and felt retarded, but oh well...

 

 

 

 

 

 

Then we all dicked around per usual, and everyone enjoyed a drunk dial from the missing Ryan. Saturday we got up and went to the Battle of the Bands, and it was nice because the sun was finally fucking out, and it wasn't raining and cold. It was great because it was free, and there was only like 150 people there to watch Sugarcult. I enjoy them, it's not like they are my favorite band or anything, but i enjoyed being a foot away from them, and they played a good live show.

 

 

We talked to the band for a bit after they were done, and he made fun of me when i asked him to sign a dollar bill. He was like, ''Wait, let me get this straight, a girl wearing an ANTI-FLAG shirt wants me to sign a DOLLAR BILL?'' So, after i slapped him in the face with my cock he made George Washington into Joey Ramone and signed it. The lead singer guy was not as chatty with us, but he had some awesome tattoos.

So after this we ate, and then went to the Chapel to see Daniel Killon who was fucking HILARIOUS, and David Allen Grier, who was funny but not as funny, in our opinions. Then we went bowling and fucked around and such. Today i layed in the sun and read, and now I'm craving some chocolate, and eventually have to write a paper. Good times! Peace Bitches!

First week of May Term has proved to be more demanding than i thought, but i am keeping really busy, and hopefully i will end up doing well in the class. It sucks though because i have class monday, tuesday, thursday, AND friday, whereas most people have just monday through thursday...Anyway the weather has been shit since i have been back. I am truly disappointed in the amount of rain in Southern California. Ridiculous. I have been wearing a sweatshirt and jeans ever since i got back...and i SHOULD BE BASKING IN THE SUNLIGHT ON THE FUCKING QUAD. But no. So tonight should be fun, we are going to this dinner thing for Liz and her honor society. And tomorrow should be fun as well, we have the battle of the bands all day, then Sugarcult is playing, and then we are going to see David Allen Grier in the Chapel. The best part? All free. Woot. I have been hanging out a lot with Brenna, generally getting my ass kicked at Scrabble because she is that hardcore. Last night we went and got some homemade Mexican food which was reallly good, and watched some Mariachis perform and what not. Later that night everyone was drinking margaritas, which eventually just turned into straight shot taking. Everyone got really messed up, there was puking on behalf of many people. I was actually glad for once i was sober. Then Ali went with Linda to Brockton, and came back TOTALLY fucked up. I was so worried she had alcohol poisioning, puking, crying, hyperventilating, making no sense. It was really scary but after a couple hours we calmed her down and she fell asleep. i was convinced we should have taken her to the emergency room but it turned out well, thankfully. Ive talked to ryan a couple times, and its already different. I can tell in the tone of his voice hes probably already forgotten about me, and our conversations will soon be obligatory for him, and too few and far between for me. Looks like somebody should move the fuck on eh?

OK. Back in SOCAL for my final three weeks of school. My fiction class seems cool, and of course i love the professor. Today is cloudy and shitty, and i feel lethargic after my two and a half hour nap. I went back to AZ for a week, drove Ryan to his dad's house and unpacked his shit. The rest of the break was spent trying to become employed, and it's reallly hard when you aren't 19, thus cannot serve liquor. So, basically my parents just bitched at me the entire break, and i lived in fear and paranoia that they would notice the gaping hole in my nose. My mom of course found out, and was cool with it? But i don't plan on telling my dad, atleast for awhile...However, its a weight lifted off my shoulders that i put there. It sucked not having my sister at home. I got to see Ki a couple times, not as much as i would have liked, its just hard since we live far apart and all. Carey stayed with us for a couple days, since Aunt Connie is still in the hospital, and not doing well. I went and visited her, pretty much to say goodbye. She's the only relative on my dad's side that i actually like, what are the odds? I hate hospitals, with a passion. The smells, the people, the machines, the feeling, the sterility....creeps me out.
